<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3137> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3137" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 125, 468f. ([C. Ful]vius Q. f. C. [n.] Flaccus); Obseq. 27; Chr. 354 (Aemiliano II et Flacco); Fast. Hyd. (Scipione Africano et Flacco); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; and on Scipio, Elog., CIL 1\n     .1, p. 198- Inscr. Ital. 13.3.71; CIL 1(2).2.763c; I. de Délos 4.1.1842. Scipio was elected under suspension of the law of 151 against iteration of the consulship, and given the command in Hither Spain by special vote.\n     \n      1\n     \n     After devoting much of the year to restoring discipline in the army, he proceeded to subjugate the areas which supported Numantia and begin the siege of the city (App. Ib. 84-89; Liv. Per. 57; cf. Cic. Rep. 1.17; Deiot. 19; Fam. 5.12.2; Sall. Iug. 7-9; Val. Max. 2.7.1; 8.15.7; Vell. 2.9.4; Frontin. Str. 4.1.1 and 5, 3.9, and 7.27; Plut. Mar. 3.2-3; and 13.2; TG 13.1; Apophth. Scip. Min. 15-20; Gell. 2.13.3; Flor. 1.34.8-12; Aelian. NH 11.9.5; Polyaen. 8.16.1-5; Eutrop. 4.17; Auct. Vir. Ill. 58.6; Veget. RM 1.15; 3.10; SHA, Hadr. 10.2; Oros. 5.7.4; Schol. Clun. 272 Stangl; Fest. 249 L; see Schulten, Gesch. Numantia 85-129; and below, Legates and Tribunes of the Soldiers). Flaccus received the command in Sicily in the war with the slaves (Liv. Per. 56; Obseq. 27; Oros. 5.9.6)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3137 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3123> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3123" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Lepidus Porcina in Hither Spain (App. Ib. 81)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3123 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3122> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3122" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Flaccus may possibly be identified with either C. Fulvius, Cos. 134, or M. Fulvius, Cos. 125 (RE 53 and 58, resp.)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3122 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3102> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3102" ;
